text: Vincent Mhlanga was a Swazi politician. He was the acting Prime Minister of Swaziland from September 7, 2018 to October 27, 2018. He was a managing director at the Kingâ€™s Office. On September 4, 2018, Prime Minister Barnabas Dlamini resigned, Mhlanga was named Acting Prime Minister and began his duties on September 7. He left office on October 27, 2018 when Ambrose Mandvulo Dlamini took office. He died from COVID-19 on 24 December 2020. ==References== Category:2020 deaths Category:Prime Ministers of Eswatini Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic Category:20th-century births Category:Year of birth unknown
